it would make you crazy.

15:30.928 --> 15:34.463
I'm feeling death right now.

15:54.851 --> 15:56.250
This place is so small,

15:56.252 --> 15:59.186
it makes the middle
of nowhere seem exciting.

15:59.188 --> 16:00.588
So I made my usual calls

16:00.590 --> 16:02.656
and just heard back
from the county sheriff.

16:02.658 --> 16:06.460
Now, he knows all about Steve
and Christy's property

16:06.462 --> 16:09.396
and says the land used to be
owned by another sheriff,

16:09.398 --> 16:12.733
that is until he lost everything
during an arrest gone bad.

16:20.075 --> 16:21.808
Now, you mentioned on the phone
that one of the owners

16:21.810 --> 16:24.278
of my clients' land
was also a sheriff.

16:24.280 --> 16:26.747
Yes, sir. His name was
Walter Hollingsworth.

16:26.749 --> 16:29.816
He's very well-liked
within the town

16:29.818 --> 16:31.619
You know, they describe him
as a tall man

16:31.621 --> 16:32.820
with a lot of nervous energy.

16:32.822 --> 16:35.423
In 1908, he married his wife,

16:35.425 --> 16:36.890
Birdie, and the two
of them of them

16:36.892 --> 16:39.960
eventually had five kids.

16:39.962 --> 16:42.163
Okay, so now, before he comes
the sheriff,

16:42.165 --> 16:44.098
was he a deputy
or anything like that?
No, sir.

16:44.100 --> 16:47.101
Sheriff Hollingsworth was
a really religious guy.

16:47.103 --> 16:48.902
He was known as a preacher.

16:48.904 --> 16:52.906
Sheriff Hollingsworth decided
to run for sheriff in 1914.

16:52.908 --> 16:54.842
He believed that he could do
more good

16:54.844 --> 16:58.446
as a lawman than a preacher.

16:58.448 --> 16:59.647
So now, you mentioned
on the phone

16:59.649 --> 17:00.981
that things went pretty bad
for him

17:00.983 --> 17:02.383
when an arrest went wrong.

17:02.385 --> 17:03.584
What happened?

17:03.586 --> 17:05.653
I'm sure, Steve,
when you was driving in,

17:05.655 --> 17:07.854
you noticed close
to your clients' property

17:07.856 --> 17:10.523
that there was a woman's
prison out there.

17:10.526 --> 17:13.928
Used to be a boy's
reformatory school.

17:13.930 --> 17:14.994
Okay.

17:14.997 --> 17:18.332
In 1931, there was a subject
in the jail

17:18.334 --> 17:21.002
that was very mentally
unstable.

17:21.003 --> 17:23.671
Well, Sheriff Hollingsworth
went back to try to subdue him,

17:23.673 --> 17:25.071
and during the fight,

17:25.074 --> 17:29.810
the jail doctor came to try
to help Sheriff Hollingsworth,

17:29.812 --> 17:34.281
and he swung a metal pipe
trying to hit the offender

17:34.283 --> 17:35.349
and wound up striking

17:35.351 --> 17:37.284
Sheriff Hollingsworth
in the head.

17:37.286 --> 17:39.086
All right.

17:39.088 --> 17:41.756
So he gets hit with friendly
fire from a steel pipe?

17:41.758 --> 17:45.359
Absolutely, and the injuries
were brutal.

17:45.361 --> 17:47.294
- Does he die on the scene?
- No.

17:47.296 --> 17:51.132
He actually goes to
a sanitarium in Waco,

17:51.134 --> 17:53.234
but with all
the brain swelling,

17:53.236 --> 17:55.770
he had to have
a portion of it removed.

17:55.772 --> 17:57.171
All right.
So what happened?

17:57.173 --> 18:01.042
He continued on as sheriff,
and in 1933,

18:01.044 --> 18:03.377
he bought
your clients' property.

18:03.379 --> 18:04.845
Okay. All right.

18:04.847 --> 18:06.180
But within a year,

18:06.182 --> 18:12.119
he died due to the complication
from his injury.

18:12.121 --> 18:15.723
I'm seeing
this crying man again.

18:15.725 --> 18:19.593
He's really stressed out.

18:19.595 --> 18:24.532
I do think, like, he was,
like, really religious.

18:24.534 --> 18:26.133
I think he's got, like,
I'm thinking

18:26.135 --> 18:28.202
it's the Bible with him.

18:28.204 --> 18:30.470
God. I feel sick.!

18:30.472 --> 18:32.339
He's super anxious,
really, like,

18:32.341 --> 18:34.541
super high-energy anxious dude.

18:39.415 --> 18:43.016
He said the economy
was really bad.-

18:43.018 --> 18:44.751
So he was murdered.

18:44.753 --> 18:47.421
But I don't know where.

18:50.360 --> 18:51.759
All right, so now, he's dead,

18:51.761 --> 18:53.994
and he's got a wife
and, what, five kids?

18:53.996 --> 18:55.896
- Yes.
- So what happened with them?

18:55.898 --> 18:58.432
Birdie, his wife, actually was
appointed sheriff

18:58.434 --> 18:59.900
and completed his term.

18:59.902 --> 19:01.301
Female sheriff?

19:01.303 --> 19:05.105
The first and only female
sheriff here in Coryell County.

19:05.107 --> 19:07.775
- Okay.
- Unfortunately, money was tight.

19:07.777 --> 19:10.311
Right.
You know, being in the middle
of the Great Depression,

19:10.313 --> 19:12.713
she had to relinquish
that property.

19:12.715 --> 19:17.785
She wound up dying nearby
in 1953 at the age of 68,

19:17.787 --> 19:21.122
and that's a photo of her.

19:21.124 --> 19:22.523
She don't look too happy?

19:22.525 --> 19:24.458
No, she looks pretty hurt.

19:31.067 --> 19:33.868
So there is
a dead woman here.

19:33.870 --> 19:35.803
She lived here for a long time.

19:35.805 --> 19:37.337
I feel like she knows
this place.

19:37.339 --> 19:38.538
You know what I'm saying?

19:38.540 --> 19:41.876
And I probably say
she's probably, like,

19:41.878 --> 19:45.946
late 70s, early 80s?

19:45.948 --> 19:51.151
Like, I almost want to put her
in the '40s or '50s, maybe.

19:54.223 --> 19:59.893
She's saying the guy with
the Bible outside comes inside.

19:59.895 --> 20:04.098
She said, "He bothers them.
He bothers them a lot."

20:08.370 --> 20:12.773
And she's like, "He will stand
there all night and just

20:12.775 --> 20:16.510
****, like, preach."

20:16.512 --> 20:19.847
That freaks out
the living people here.

20:19.849 --> 20:22.183
They're hearing him talking,

20:22.185 --> 20:25.986
and they're feeling his energy.

20:25.988 --> 20:28.922
They're freaking out
because he overwhelms them.

20:28.924 --> 20:30.657
He overwhelms them.

