21:06.260 --> 21:08.594
So here's an interesting fact
about this city.

21:08.596 --> 21:10.929
About 15,000 people live here,

21:10.931 --> 21:13.132
and more than half of them
are locked up.

21:13.134 --> 21:15.134
Now, Christy was a guard
at that big prison

21:15.136 --> 21:17.937
down the street from her house,
so I called a local author

21:17.939 --> 21:20.672
who said it used to be
a boy's reformatory,

21:20.674 --> 21:22.808
and what went on there
was so shocking,

21:22.810 --> 21:24.210
it will definitely
help my case.

21:32.086 --> 21:33.552
Well, Dr. Bush, thanks
for meeting me here.

21:33.554 --> 21:34.687
I appreciate that.

21:34.689 --> 21:37.022
Before we get to what went wrong
at the school,

21:37.024 --> 21:38.357
how did it even start?

21:38.359 --> 21:41.694
It opened because of a group
of Christian women reformers

21:41.696 --> 21:44.296
who had been visiting
all of the prisons in Texas

21:44.298 --> 21:46.298
to check on
the conditions there,

21:46.300 --> 21:49.101
and they discovered
all of these teenage boys

21:49.103 --> 21:51.704
in the prisons
with the adult prisoners,

21:51.706 --> 21:55.241
so in 1889,
68 boys were transferred out of

21:55.243 --> 21:57.910
the Texas prisons
into Gatesville,

21:57.912 --> 21:59.245
and I have a picture
of it right here

21:59.247 --> 22:02.915
to give you a sense
of what it looked like.

22:02.917 --> 22:04.316
When did it go bad?

22:04.318 --> 22:06.451
It started going bad pretty much
right from the beginning --

22:06.453 --> 22:09.121
a lot of fighting,
a lot of violence,

22:09.123 --> 22:12.858
definitely reports
of inmate rape.

22:12.860 --> 22:14.459
What were their living
conditions like?

22:14.461 --> 22:16.662
They had these sort of
mass-custody dorms.

22:16.664 --> 22:18.397
I've got a picture
of one of them here.

22:18.399 --> 22:21.734
You can see it's just rows
and rows of beds.

22:21.736 --> 22:24.069
It's almost like
a hospital ward.

22:24.071 --> 22:26.071
So there's a lot of
overcrowding there.

22:26.073 --> 22:27.539
It was really unsanitary,

22:27.541 --> 22:30.075
so you had disease epidemics
break out.

22:30.077 --> 22:33.045
In 1918 when
the Spanish Flu epidemic

22:33.047 --> 22:36.348
swept the United States,
300 boys in Gatesville

22:36.350 --> 22:39.284
caught it,
and eight of them died.

22:39.286 --> 22:42.554
Another eight died
in accidents,

22:42.556 --> 22:44.757
other sicknesses
that could've been prevented

22:44.759 --> 22:46.491
if conditions had been better.

22:46.493 --> 22:48.493
What happens to their bodies?
Their family take them?

22:48.495 --> 22:50.495
There was actually a cemetery

22:50.497 --> 22:53.766
that still exists
on the grounds today.

22:53.768 --> 22:55.367
So I know it eventually
closed down,

22:55.369 --> 22:58.036
and now, it's a women's prison,
from what I understand.

22:58.038 --> 23:01.307
In '79, it shut down,
and the very next year in 1980,

23:01.309 --> 23:03.308
it reopened
as a women's prison.

23:07.648 --> 23:13.185
There's, like, all of these
very old brown skeletons.

23:13.187 --> 23:18.857
They just are to the side of,
like, this path,

23:18.859 --> 23:23.529
and I see a hundred men
facing the road,

23:23.531 --> 23:26.866
and all of them turn
at the same time.

23:26.868 --> 23:28.066
They're all men.

23:28.068 --> 23:29.734
They're all male,
and they're pointing,

23:29.736 --> 23:32.738
and what they're pointing at
is where the church should be,

23:32.740 --> 23:35.874
and all of a sudden,
all these walls come up,

23:35.876 --> 23:38.444
like these cement walls,

23:38.446 --> 23:40.812
and then I feel like it
was a trick,

23:40.814 --> 23:46.017
and I got duped,
and I'm trapped.

23:46.019 --> 23:50.089
The snake, that thing, that man,
it's causing violence.

23:50.091 --> 23:54.359
Any negative things
that living have done here

23:54.361 --> 23:55.628
was because of him.

23:59.901 --> 24:02.701
Since the reformatory
closed in 1979,

24:02.703 --> 24:04.369
there have got to be
some people in town

24:04.371 --> 24:05.770
who used to be inmates there.

24:05.772 --> 24:08.106
So I worked the phones, talked
to a bunch of the locals,

24:08.108 --> 24:10.375
and I finally got in touch
with one guy

24:10.377 --> 24:12.778
who says the experience
was so horrible,

24:12.780 --> 24:13.846
he's never gotten over it.

24:20.254 --> 24:21.854
Obviously, this school
was a big deal

24:21.856 --> 24:24.256
to have a whole wing
to it in this museum.

24:24.258 --> 24:26.792
I don't mean to pry, but I need
to know if you can tell me.

24:26.794 --> 24:28.326
How the hell did you wind
up in here?

24:28.328 --> 24:30.062
Truancy, believe it or not.

24:30.064 --> 24:31.530
All right.
So let me get this straight.

24:31.532 --> 24:33.599
You wound up in prison
because you didn't go to school?

24:33.601 --> 24:34.934
You skipped out of school?

24:34.936 --> 24:36.802
I mean would've been in jail
at 11.

24:36.804 --> 24:39.204
What year did you get
sentenced here?
1975.

24:39.206 --> 24:40.739
I was 15.

24:40.741 --> 24:43.075
I just spoke to a professor
who told me

24:43.077 --> 24:44.676
that the conditions
were barbaric there.

24:44.678 --> 24:45.944
What was it like
when you were there?

24:45.946 --> 24:48.213
You could've called it
a gladiator farm.

24:48.215 --> 24:50.816
In order to have any kind
of respect

24:50.818 --> 24:54.486
with any of the kids there, you
had to stand up for yourself.

24:54.488 --> 24:55.888
Otherwise, you would be
eaten alive.

24:55.890 --> 24:58.156
And it's not something
you get out of your head.

24:58.158 --> 25:00.226
No. I still think about that.

25:00.228 --> 25:02.428
Did you ever attempt
to get out of this place?

25:02.430 --> 25:04.563
More times than
I can probably count.

25:04.565 --> 25:06.965
Okay, when you escaped,
what was it like?

25:06.967 --> 25:11.436
Somewhere between terrifying
and exhilarating.

25:11.438 --> 25:13.839
Your heart is racing
100 miles an hour.

25:13.841 --> 25:16.508
The horsemen, we heard them
as they were approaching

25:16.510 --> 25:18.777
because you could hear them
talking on their walkie-talkies.

25:18.779 --> 25:22.515
You could hear the dogs baying,
absolutely terrifying.

25:22.517 --> 25:24.183
It's the run for your life,

25:24.185 --> 25:26.852
and you knew that
if they caught you

25:26.854 --> 25:30.523
that you were going to take
a pretty hardcore beating

25:30.525 --> 25:32.257
or get killed.

25:32.259 --> 25:34.326
So, obviously,
you got picked up.
Yes.

25:34.328 --> 25:37.730
Unfortunately, the Coryell
County Sheriff's Department,

25:37.732 --> 25:41.000
the state guys, they were
all on top of us like crazy.

25:41.002 --> 25:43.335
So do you know of anyone
personally

25:43.337 --> 25:45.938
that didn't make it back
from one of these escapes?

25:45.940 --> 25:49.808
There was a kid on our dorm
that didn't make it back.

25:49.810 --> 25:52.144
I believe it happened
to a lot of kids.

25:52.146 --> 25:55.147
I believe some of them
are still on the grounds.

25:55.149 --> 25:56.282
I really do.

25:56.284 --> 25:58.484
Do you think you ever got
over your time here?

25:58.486 --> 26:00.085
No, probably not.

26:00.087 --> 26:02.554
It took me a long time
to get to where

26:02.556 --> 26:05.290
I didn't sleep
with one eye open.

26:05.292 --> 26:09.828
I think it's haunted a lot of
people, and it still haunts me.

26:20.374 --> 26:23.642
I saw a lot of disturbing things
during my walk,

26:23.644 --> 26:26.512
but the snakelike creature
tormenting the living

26:26.514 --> 26:28.847
has me the most concerned.

26:28.849 --> 26:33.918
It was
this gray nonhuman thing.

26:33.920 --> 26:38.757
He had, like, pin-straight hair,
like, an abnormally thin neck,

26:38.759 --> 26:43.862
leaning over a person in a bed,
and he turned into a snake.

26:46.467 --> 26:49.267
I would make that
a little bit wider...

26:49.269 --> 26:50.468
- Wider?
- Yeah.

26:50.470 --> 26:52.605
...and not too much
nostril here.
Okay.

26:58.946 --> 27:02.014
Amy, is this what you saw?

27:02.016 --> 27:03.415
Yes.

27:28.974 --> 27:31.842
Now that Amy and I have
completed our investigations,

27:31.844 --> 27:34.711
we're ready to reveal
our findings to each other

27:34.713 --> 27:37.581
and our clients
for the first time.

27:37.583 --> 27:40.250
So, Amy, this is Christy,
and this is her husband, Steve.

27:40.252 --> 27:42.785
They live here together,
and this is Tiffany,

27:42.787 --> 27:44.254
Christy's daughter.

27:44.256 --> 27:46.856
Now, I got to tell you.
Christy's story broke my heart.

27:46.858 --> 27:48.525
She believes whatever here
is evil

27:48.527 --> 27:51.461
and hates women and children,
and that's a huge problem

27:51.463 --> 27:54.530
because Christy has four
beautiful grandchildren.

27:56.801 --> 27:59.669
Now, these kids visit a lot,

27:59.671 --> 28:01.871
so she's hoping you can show her
what's here

28:01.873 --> 28:04.207
and how to kick it out.

28:04.209 --> 28:06.476
So now that Amy knows a little
bit about you guys,

28:06.478 --> 28:08.211
she'll tell us about her walk.

28:14.886 --> 28:17.754
There's an extreme amount
of negative energy

28:17.756 --> 28:20.090
here in this area.

28:20.092 --> 28:23.560
I was feeling multiple deaths
that had occurred,

28:23.562 --> 28:26.029
very violent deaths
that were nearby.

28:26.031 --> 28:31.568
I was shown a lot of really
old bones,

28:31.570 --> 28:34.036
and they were all scattered.

28:34.038 --> 28:35.572
The next thing was,

28:35.574 --> 28:40.444
I saw about a hundred people.

28:40.446 --> 28:43.713
They were pointing towards
what should be a church,

28:43.715 --> 28:46.182
but it was in ruins.

28:46.184 --> 28:48.518
Then these large cement walls

28:48.520 --> 28:53.590
just came up on all four sides
and just blocked me in.

28:53.592 --> 28:55.392
A lot of what you mentioned
makes me think of the prison

28:55.394 --> 28:56.793
right down the road from here.

28:56.795 --> 28:59.062
Now, Christy, actually,
you worked there, right?

29:00.532 --> 29:03.200
So these days, it's a maximum
security women's prison.

29:03.202 --> 29:04.668
Really?

29:04.670 --> 29:07.203
But back in the day, it was
a boy's reformatory school.

29:07.205 --> 29:08.404
Interesting.

29:08.406 --> 29:11.040
Now, you mentioned
that you saw a church.

29:11.042 --> 29:15.678
It was started in the late 1800s
by a woman's Christian group.

29:15.680 --> 29:17.013
The goal of this whole thing
was to help

29:17.015 --> 29:19.148
troubled kids
turn their lives around.

29:19.150 --> 29:22.285
Instead, it turned
into a nightmare.

29:22.287 --> 29:26.088
They were abused, beaten,
raped, tortured.

29:26.090 --> 29:28.759
How could anyone do that
to children?

29:28.761 --> 29:32.162
Conditions were so bad there,
16 kids died in a 20-year period

29:32.164 --> 29:35.298
from 1900 to 1920.

29:35.300 --> 29:37.634
The kids were buried
right on the grounds

29:37.636 --> 29:41.638
just down the street from here.

29:41.640 --> 29:45.709
Cemetery's still there today.

29:45.711 --> 29:47.510
Now, the abuse
went on for years.

29:47.512 --> 29:51.514
Finally, the Feds came in,
and in 1979, they shut it down.

29:51.516 --> 29:54.851
I heard stories,
and I didn't know what was true

29:54.853 --> 29:56.253
and what wasn't true.

30:00.225 --> 30:03.126
Okay. So what else?

30:03.128 --> 30:07.130
One of the dead people
that I ran into

30:07.132 --> 30:11.868
was a deceased little girl.

30:11.870 --> 30:15.939
I was guessing her age
at about 8 years.

30:15.941 --> 30:19.142
Living people in this house
might see her.

30:19.144 --> 30:20.610
That's interesting.

30:20.612 --> 30:23.146
Tiffany, did you tell me about
having a dream of a little girl?

30:23.148 --> 30:24.948
I did.

30:24.950 --> 30:26.616
She had long blonde hair.

30:26.618 --> 30:29.152
I didn't see what she was
wearing or anything,

30:29.154 --> 30:31.554
but she did
have solid black eyes.

30:31.556 --> 30:32.688
Interesting.

30:32.690 --> 30:36.158
She spends a lot of time
in the master bedroom.

30:36.160 --> 30:41.431
She also was showing me
that she would get into bed

30:41.433 --> 30:43.833
and crawl kind of
to the bottom of the bed

30:43.835 --> 30:47.437
and curl up like
a little dog.

30:47.439 --> 30:49.172
I was laying in bed,

30:49.174 --> 30:53.777
and I felt like something
was definitely in the bed.

30:59.117 --> 31:03.320
The next dead person I ran into
was just freaking out,

31:03.322 --> 31:05.989
so I call him the crying man.

31:05.991 --> 31:09.125
He has a very big impact

31:09.127 --> 31:12.128
on the living in this house.

31:12.130 --> 31:16.600
He has extremely high anxiety.

31:16.602 --> 31:20.804
He can easily affect the living
and their emotions

31:20.806 --> 31:22.672
when they're around him,

31:22.674 --> 31:27.077
so that could swing
from extreme stress and anxiety

31:27.079 --> 31:29.078
to extreme depression,

31:29.080 --> 31:33.950
possibly even the need
to cry unexpectedly.

31:33.952 --> 31:39.356
I go from crying to large
bouts of depression,

31:39.358 --> 31:43.359
sadness, anxiety,
and there's lots of anger,

31:43.361 --> 31:46.228
constant roller coaster
of emotions.

31:46.230 --> 31:48.899
So, Tiffany, when you're here,
do you feel that?
Yes.

31:48.901 --> 31:53.770
I feel sad and especially
in the back room.

31:53.772 --> 31:57.240
Now, you used to live back
in that room?
Yes, I did.

31:57.242 --> 31:59.308
He talks a lot,

31:59.310 --> 32:02.912
so I thought that maybe
the living here would hear him.

32:02.914 --> 32:04.380
Tell Amy what happened.

32:04.382 --> 32:06.650
I was sitting out on the porch
one night,

32:06.652 --> 32:09.652
and it sounded like a man
